properties.name: 360 - Alton Village
properties.description:
name: Alton Village
description: Alton Village was built in 2006, Alton Village, with the goal of creating an urban design with an attractive street-scape. Located on the Niagara Escarpment, Alton Village provides its residents with parks, community centres, schools, and shopping centres.

properties.name: 355 - Corporate
properties.description:
name: Corporate
description: The Corporate neighbourhood began in the early 2000's, and consists mostly of town houses, semi detached homes and condos.  A great place to retire if you want a smaller home, or perfect for the commuter.  There are no schools in this area, so it's not ideal for young families.

properties.name: 354 - Tansley Woods
properties.description:
name: Tansley Woods
description: The Tansley Woods is another new neighbourhood in Burlington as it was constructed in the late 1990's. This Burlington neighbourhood is made up of a variety of semi-detached, detached, townhouses and condominium homes.   It is perfect for singles and families as there are so many restaurants and shops nearby.

properties.name: 353 - Palmer
properties.description:
name: Palmer
description: The Palmer neighbourhood was constructed in the late 1990's and is very family-friendly with its abundance of restaurants and shopping opportunities. This Burlington neighbourhood is family-friendly and offers a wide variety of restaurant and shopping options. A variety of semi-detached, detached, townhouses and condominium homes are what make up this family friendly neighbourhood.

properties.name: 352 - The Orchard
properties.description:
name: The Orchard
description: The Orchard is a newer community, with newer homes.  It's proximity to Fortinos and Bronte Creek Provincial Park make this a great spot for people on the go, who like to hit the trails, without driving a couple hours up north.

properties.name: 351 - Millcroft
properties.description:
name: Millcroft
description: Millcroft is a 3,200 home neighbourhood built around the Millcroft Golf and Country Club.  A great place for retirement if you are a golfer.  The homes were built in the 80's, meaning that they are in great shape.

properties.name: 350 - Headon Forest
properties.description:
name: Headon Forest
description: The Headon Forest Neighbourhood in Burlington Ontario was built in the mid 1980's. This neighbourhood community offers a wide variety of family housing close to a variety of shopping areas, parks and schools. Most of the homes have large lots, making it perfect for raising a family (lots of opportunities for backyard get-togethers and birthday parties.)

properties.name: 342 - Mountainside
properties.description:
name: Mountainside
description: The Mountainside Neighbourhood is named after it's short distance to the Hamilton Mountain.  Houses are mature here, and feature large lots.  It's very close to Costco, making it great for young families.

properties.name: 341 - Brant Hills
properties.description:
name: Brant Hills
description: Brant Hills is a family oriented area filled with parks, trails and schools. Great for kids, as it has the Brant Hills Park, as well as a nearby location to the Bruce Trail.  It's also close to two golf courses, making it ideal for raising a family and relaxation.

properties.name: 332 - Elizabeth Gardens
properties.description:
name: Elizabeth Gardens
description: Elizabeth Gardens borders on the edge of Oakville.  There are many homes available if you want a lakeshore property in this area.  It is a beautiful neighbourhood with lots of parks.

properties.name: 331 - Shoreacres
properties.description:
name: Shoreacres
description: Shoreacres in  Burlington is known for some of the most unique houses in the city.  You'll find several parks in this area, as well as the popular Paletta Mansion.

properties.name: 330 - Roseland
properties.description:
name: Roseland
description: This neighbourhood has a lot of older homes that require a little remodeling.  This is prime real estate, and property values are high for lakeshore living.  The neighbourhood has lots of old, tall trees which provide beauty and privacy.

properties.name: 322 - Pinedale
properties.description:
name: Pinedale
description: The Pinedale community combines both old and new housing, ot make for a very family oriented neighbourhood.  The Appleby Go Station Rail, and Appleby Mall make this  a great spot to live for commuters and their family

properties.name: 321 - Longmoor
properties.description:
name: Longmoor
description: Longmoor is a great spot to live, particularly if you are single.  This area features several restaurants, and coffee shops.  It's also very close to the Go Station.

properties.name: 320 - Dynes
properties.description:
name: Dynes
description: The Dynes Community has it all.  There are residential homes, amazing restaurants, and of course the Burlington Mall.  A nice neighbourhood to raise a family in, particularly if you have teens as the Mall is very close.

properties.name: 312 - Central Burlington
properties.description:
name: Central Burlington
description: Central Burlington is essentially where Burlington built itself up from. This older community has a lot of character and history.  You'll find the Tennis Club and Central Park in Central Burlington, along with Emma's Back Porch which has an amazing lakeside view.

name: Aldershot
description: Aldershot features lots of greenery, as well as many community resources, shops, and of course the Aldershot Go-Station.
